node.text:
I’ve decided that I really like making cooking videos! Minus the fact that I still get awkward and say dumb things. But it’s fun to get creative and make things up as I go! 

These came out awesome. I adjusted some things in the written recipe, so go off of that! Full recipe below: 

2 lbs green beans (trimmed and rinsed)
2 tablespoons liquid aminos 
2 teaspoons sesame oil 
1 teaspoon minced garlic 
1 tablespoon sweetener 
1/4 cup avocado oil 
Onion powder
Garlic salt
Salt and pepper

Mix altogether and air fry for 15 minutes on 400°. (Stir the beans halfway through the cooking time.)

Watch now, bookmark it for later cause these are bomb! Thanks so much for watching! ♥️

I ended up not changing anything about this recipe! I poured the remainder of the sauce on top and it was perfect! 

See some helpful tips at the bottom 👇🏽

Ingredients: 
2 lbs packaged coleslaw 
1 cup Mayo
2/3 cup unsweetened coconut milk 
2 tablespoons sweetener 
2 tablespoons Apple Cider Vinegar 
1 tablespoon lemon juice 
1 teaspoon horseradish 
Salt and pepper 
Green onions for garnish 

* Friendly reminder- eggs are not dairy (in reference to the Mayo. Mayo is made from eggs and olive oil.) 
* Coconut milk from the can is much thicker than the cartons
* Be sure to grab UNSWEETENED coconut milk 
* If you’re a horseradish fan, double the amount. You’ll love it. 
* My favorite sweetener is from @lakanto. Code KMS20 saves you 20% 

I hope you try this! It’s so simple and fresh!

New year, new you doesn’t have to wait until January. Let’s crush it now and start living the life you deserve. ♥️

Sausage balls! 🤩

Perfect for meal prep, packed lunches, or food on the go. 

You need: 
2 lbs ground breakfast sausage 
8 ounces cream cheese, softened
1 1/2 cups shredded cheddar
3/4 cup almond flour 
Garlic and onion powder 

 Mix altogether, form into balls, bake for 25 mins on 350°. 

I love mine with some sugar free syrup. I use @choczero. Discount code is KETOMADESIMPLE 

Enjoy! ♥️

node.text:
5 minute Alfredo! Yes please. 

Our family loves meals like this. Quick and easy. Zero skill required. 👌🏽

Full recipe: 
1/2 stick butter
Garlic (however much you like)
3 ounces cream cheese 
1 1/2 cups heavy cream 
1 cup Parmesan cheese 
Salt and pepper, to taste 

1. Over medium heat, melt the butter, cream cheese, and garlic. 
2. Whisk in the heavy cream and bring to a boil. 
4. Slowly stir in the Parmesan cheese whisk until fully dissolved. Season with salt and pepper. 

I served mine over steamed broccoli and rotisserie chicken. Absolutely delicious. 

Tag a friend who would love this! 

Happy Sunday!

node.text:
Keto friendly Costco items! 

I found a couple new items today that I’m excited to try! 

Just a friendly reminder to always check the labels. If being “keto friendly” was determined on a scale of 1-10, a lot of these keto labeled foods would be a 5, at best. Ahem, parm crisps made with maltodextrin. If you haven’t had your first maltodextrin experience yet, you’re in for it. Bubble guts for days. (So why do I keep buying them? I DONT KNOW, MIND YA BUSINESS) 😂🙈

Anyway, I don’t eat perfectly, but I definitely try to help educate, so that you can decide for yourself how you’d like to approach a ketogenic lifestyle. 

Regardless of the product, I’m grateful for all these Keto companies who have helped provide a way for me sustain this lifestyle! As the keto community continues to grow, we will keep seeing more and more items on the shelves. TRY THEM ALL! 

What’s your must have keto product at Costco? (Or anywhere else) 

Okay, that’s all. Love you, bye.

node.text:
Super simple Pot Roast! 🧅🥕

Every time I post things like this, I get a lot of not-so-nice comments. First about carrots. Second about the crap ingredients in that onion soup packet. 

I’ll address both. 

Carrots are totally okay on keto. In moderation. Carrots are one of the more starchy veggies out there, but incorporating a few is perfectly fine. (A cup of carrots is roughly 9 net carbs.) I’ll let you decide whether you’d like to eat them or not. Same goes for onions. 

The ingredients in this Onion Soup packet are not awesome. Normally I would make my own out of a few spices. Today I wanted the shortcut! 

Just a friendly reminder that we can all do keto a million different ways and still achieve results. I eat with budget in mind first (usually). So I opt for “dirty keto” occasionally and it works for us, our budget, and our tastebuds. 

Please do what works for you! If I still see those kinds of comments, I’ll just assume you didn’t make it this far in the caption. 😆

I still love you! Happy Wednesday!

node.text:
Chicken Parm! 🤌🏽

If you’ve never marinated your chicken in Mayo, you’re missing out!!!!! It makes the chicken extremely tender. 

You may need to adjust the cook time depending on how much chicken you’re cooking. I had a full pan, so mine took around 40 minutes. Just make sure your chicken is over 165° F and it’s done. 

And for the parents who don’t want to eat separate meals than your family, give them noodles or garlic bread or something. They’ll love it. Perfect family meal. Everyone wins.

node.text:
I’d also like to add to this list… get out of your own head! 

You’re most likely overthinking it. I promise. There’s endless amounts of keto content available at your fingertips, but that can feel soooooo overwhelming!!! Trust me. I get it. 

My best advice is to just start! You’ll make mistakes. But I promise that when you start to pay attention to how good being in ketosis makes you feel, you’ll gravitate towards it and it’ll just get easier and easier. 

I want you to be able to come to my page and find something you can instantly make with ingredients you already have on hand. 

I want you to be able to search my page and find the answers to the random questions you have. 

Most of all, I want you to feel supported in your journey, especially if you don’t have the support from those who are in your daily life. 

So this is what I’m asking you to do: 

1. Comment with what your goals are. 
2. Let me know how I can help you achieve those goals. 

✌🏽♥️
